**Lapse rate** refers to the `rate at which temperature decreases with an increase in altitude`. {.bar}

It is usually expressed in **degrees Celsius per kilometer (┬░C/km)**.

The amount of temperature decrease depends on the **type of air or gas** (dry, moist, or mixed) and the **location** in the atmosphere.
